{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13854: Import Over a Certain File Size Throws Error",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:16:02.927391+00:00",
  "text": "Import Over a Certain File Size Throws Error\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.21\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://github.com/incutonez/issues/blob/main/Import%20Error%20with%20Large%20File%20Size.7z\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Download and extract zip file\n- `npm i`\n- Open `src/index.ts` and notice that the first line has an error saying `Cannot find module '@/MyImage.vue' or its corresponding type declarations.ts(2307)`\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe error shouldn't show... it's basically the same as MyImage2, except it's a bit larger in size, so I believe it has to do with some sort of file size limitation in a parser somewhere?\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nWe get this error, and I can't run vue-tsc properly, as it fails compilation with the same error.\n\n<img width=\"1920\" height=\"1032\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8ddd4dc8-b5a5-4c7a-9b9e-4a22116e94f4\" />\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\n  OS: Windows 11 10.0.22631\nBinaries:\n  Node: 22.19.0\n  npm: 10.9.3\nnpmPackages:\n  vue: ^3.5.21 => 3.5.21\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types",
    "language-tools"
  ],
